title: National League strugglers Aldershot Town and Dagenham & Redbridge play out a goalless draw.
title_page: National League strugglers Aldershot Town and Dagenham & Redbridge play out a goalless draw. - BBC Sport
maintext:
National League strugglers Aldershot and Dagenham & Redbridge shared the points from a drab goalless draw.
Dagenham had the best chance of the night only three minutes in when Josh Rees struck the post at the end of a swift counter-attack, having been set up by Ryan Hill.
But there was otherwise little to separate two sides who are hovering just above the relegation zone.
Aldershot's best chance came late in the first half when Ryan Jones saw a close-range header kept out from a corner.
